INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (224, 1, '2014-09-14 16:00:42', '2014-09-14 16:00:42', 'Debbie Kaufmann joined Lifematters in January 2014 as a part-time employee, and in August 2014, was retained on a full time basis. In addition to assisting CEO Scott Thompson with his administrative needs, she serves as Director of Communications, developing internal communications programs to ensure Lifematters’ employees and caregivers are involved, informed, and engaged. Debbie will also work on external communications programs to help educate the public on the importance of home care and ways in which to navigate finding the right caregiver for one’s self or loved one.\r\n\r\nDebbie has more than 25 years of experience in corporate and marketing communications and public relations. She spent years working in a range of communications positions in the telecommunications industry, and from 2002-2009, she directed corporate communications for three US pharmaceutical subsidiaries of Otsuka Pharmaceuticals Co., Ltd, a Japanese pharmaceutical and healthcare-related company comprised of pharmaceutical and food &amp; beverage-related companies around the world. Debbie also has a history in working with advocacy groups in an effort to help patients, physicians and caregivers in various therapeutic areas. In addition, Debbie helped launch and grow Gator Ron’s Zesty Sauces &amp; Mixes, a specialty food company manufacturing and selling products developed by her business partner’s late husband Ron Griffith, who died of ALS, which was established to raise money for ALS Research. Debbie was actively involved in the selection of caregivers, and the care, of both her mother-in-law and her mother, and is personally passionate about the importance of what Lifematters does.\r\n\r\nDebbie has a Bachelor of Science degree from the University of Maryland. She lives in Bethesda, Maryland with her husband and two cats. An avid reader, her hobbies also include entertaining, music, and learning everything she can about nutrition and healthy living.', 'Debbie Kaufmann', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'debbie-kaufmann', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:00:42', '2014-09-14 16:00:42', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=224', 19, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (225, 1, '2014-09-14 16:01:34', '2014-09-14 16:01:34', 'I joined Lifematters after 12 years in healthcare, working in nursing homes. I’m excited to be here. Everyone is very passionate about their jobs and doing them well. With four children, I keep really busy. I like to relax with Zumba!', 'Angel Freeman', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'angel-freeman', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:01:34', '2014-09-14 16:01:34', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=225', 17, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (226, 1, '2014-09-14 16:02:15', '2014-09-14 16:02:15', 'I joined Lifematters after working at an assisted living facility. The people here are great – it’s a very friendly atmosphere. I love to travel, and also to sing and dance.', 'Alexandra Fanelli', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'alexandra-fanelli', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:02:15', '2014-09-14 16:02:15', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=226', 16, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (227, 1, '2014-09-14 16:03:10', '2014-09-14 16:03:10', 'I’ve been with Lifematters for 10 years, since its very beginning. It’s my home! When I’m at my other home (where I live), I keep busy with my children. And I love the arts.', 'Rhizza Dela Cruz', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rhizza-dela-cruz', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:03:10', '2014-09-14 16:03:10', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=227', 15, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (228, 1, '2014-09-14 16:04:00', '2014-09-14 16:04:00', 'Peter Clopton is a leading expert in private duty home care for adult children (the sandwich generation) and spouses providing care to their family members. He oversees many of the staff and organizations utilizing Lifematters’ services in Maryland and Washington, D.C. Since 2009, Peter has greatly contributed to the successful growth of Lifematters in Maryland and Washington, D.C. He has achieved this by forming relationships and partnerships within the industry, meeting directly with families to personally match their needs with the appropriate caregivers, working in conjunction with the CEO, COO and management team to streamline company processes, training new employees, and creating educational presentations for leading hospitals, doctors, social workers, case managers, assisted living facilities, nursing homes and rehab communities in the region. He also authored an article providing questions families should ask when searching for a home care agency, which was featured in Bethesda Magazine.\r\n\r\nPeter is an avid member of the D.C. Senior Resource Group and the Grass Roots Organization for the Wellbeing of Seniors (GROW) which provides educational and networking opportunities for seniors, bringing together social service and government agencies, businesses, religious organizations, eldercare professionals and seniors for collaborative initiatives in addressing the needs of older adults.\r\n\r\nPeter received his Bachelor’s Degree from the University of North Carolina at Wilmington. A lifelong Washingtonian, Peter has fifteen years of management, sales and marketing experience and resides in Silver Spring, MD with his wife and three children.', 'Peter Clopton', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'peter-clopton', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:04:00', '2014-09-14 16:04:00', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=228', 14, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (229, 1, '2014-09-14 16:04:53', '2014-09-14 16:04:53', 'I love working for Lifematters! The company provides exceptional services and care for its clients. It reaches out to the communities we work in, and to the people we work for to make positive changes in their lives. I’m a mom, so I spend my free time with my children, and when I can, reading, swimming, and watching sports.', 'Dilys Chebe, RN', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dilys-chebe-rn', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:04:53', '2014-09-14 16:04:53', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=229', 13, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (230, 1, '2014-09-14 16:05:40', '2014-09-14 16:05:40', 'Kristin Chang has been the Assistant Controller with Lifematters since 2012. She brings 7 years of experience in the home health industry. Her detail-oriented nature, combined with strong analytical and problem solving skills, has enabled Kristin to supervise the accounting department while supporting operations.\r\n\r\nShe is involved in all aspects of accounts payable and receivable, payroll, accounting and tax matters, financial statements, bank and vendor account reconciliation, financial statements, budgets, and more. Prior to joining Lifematters, Kristin was a Senior Accountant for companies including theater productions, restaurants, and cafes.The diversity and work culture that Lifematters offers are attributes Kristin appreciates. Always busy, she says that at the Lifematters’ office, “there is never a dull moment.”\r\nShe received her Bachelor’s Degree in Accounting, Government &amp; Politics, as well as her Master’s Degree in Finance and Accounting, from the University of Maryland in College Park, Maryland. An avid fan of the arts and an animal lover, Kristin lives in Rockville, MD.', 'Kristin Chang', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'kristin-chang', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:05:40', '2014-09-14 16:05:40', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=230', 12, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (231, 1, '2014-09-14 16:06:27', '2014-09-14 16:06:27', 'Lifematters is a great company to grow with. I have awesome teammates, and I’m always learning more every day. It’s my second job in home care – previously I worked at a nursing home – and here, every day is a great experience.', 'Rosalinda Avalos', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rosalinda-avalos', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:06:27', '2014-09-14 16:06:27', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=231', 11, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (232, 1, '2014-09-14 16:07:27', '2014-09-14 16:07:27', 'I joined Lifematters in 2011 after working for six years in other home care companies, and it’s been such a positive experience. Everyone is a team player and so dedicated. And the people are so kind – my colleagues and my clients! When I’m not at work, I enjoy shopping, cooking, and being with my family.', 'Benedicta Amoateng', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'benedicta-amoateng', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:07:41', '2014-09-14 16:07:41', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=232', 10, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (233, 1, '2014-09-14 16:08:43', '2014-09-14 16:08:43', 'Rich Willis joined Lifematters in 2008 as a file clerk. He was quickly promoted to the accounting department, and is now a Director of Client Services and manages the Virginia office. Rich’s experience in home care began when he was his grandfather’s caregiver, taking care of his daily needs and administering his home dialysis treatments.\r\n\r\nA native of New York City, he attended Frostburg State University and now resides in a Maryland suburb of Washington, D.C.', 'Rich Willis', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'rich-willis', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:08:43', '2014-09-14 16:08:43', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=233', 8, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (234, 1, '2014-09-14 16:09:38', '2014-09-14 16:09:38', 'My colleagues at Lifematters are all about teamwork and dedication, and I can feel free to approach everyone with questions and ideas. I’m studying to pass the Licensed Practical Nursing Board, and am excited about future nursing opportunities with Lifematters.', 'Janet Thompson', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'janet-thompson', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:09:38', '2014-09-14 16:09:38', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=234', 7, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (235, 1, '2014-09-14 16:10:22', '2014-09-14 16:10:22', 'The impact that we have on our clients and their families is incredibly fulfilling. Our caregivers often become like part of the family and I love being part of an organization that makes peoples’ lives happier and better.', 'Amina Smith', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'amina-smith', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:10:22', '2014-09-14 16:10:22', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=235', 6, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (236, 1, '2014-09-14 16:11:13', '2014-09-14 16:11:13', 'I always find it very fulfilling to see the impact that Lifematters has on our clients and their families; seeing how our caregivers really care about them, and become like part of the family. It’s so nice! I love my job, and also love my hobbies: reading, hiking and baking.', 'Valerie Menke', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'valerie-menke', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:11:13', '2014-09-14 16:11:13', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=236', 5, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (237, 1, '2014-09-14 16:12:00', '2014-09-14 16:12:00', 'Lifematters is a great place to work. It’s a very family oriented environment, where we are all encouraged to work hard, be creative, and share ideas. The people I work with, office staff and caregivers, are a true team.', 'Tori Mclean', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tori-mclean', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:12:00', '2014-09-14 16:12:00', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=237', 4, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (238, 1, '2014-09-14 16:12:46', '2014-09-14 16:12:46', 'Sarah has worked in the home care industry for over a decade. At Lifematters, her primary role is working with clients and helping them and their families assess and identify their needs, and organizing the many pieces and aspects of the skilled nursing services that Lifematters provides.Sarah began her career in home care working for a small non-profit start-up agency, where she worked in every facet of the organization.  Looking to expand her knowledge and expertise, she  went on to work for Shady Grove Adventist Hospital on the orthopedic unit that specialized in joint replacements.\r\n\r\nSarah appreciates the fact that Lifematters is independently owned and operated, which she feels enables her to think creatively to provide the best services for her clients.\r\n\r\nShe attended Barton College in Wilson, NC and is also licensed as a Certified Nursing Assistant by the Maryland Board of Nursing.', 'Sarah Libby', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'sarah-libby', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:12:46', '2014-09-14 16:12:46', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=238', 3, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (239, 1, '2014-09-14 16:13:53', '2014-09-14 16:13:53', 'I have been with Lifematters since the Spring of 2013, and it’s been great. I really enjoy meeting all of our clients and developing positive relationships with them. During my non-working hours, I spend much of my time relaxing on the couch, reading  or watching Netflix, as well as going out with friends.', 'Jihoon Kim, RN', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jihoon-kim-rn', '', '', '2014-09-14 16:20:15', '2014-09-14 16:20:15', '', 0, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/?post_type=staff_mbr&#038;p=239', 2, 'staff_mbr', '', 0); 
