 is our most important asset. Each of our caregivers undergoes hours of training developed by Lifematters University – the most comprehensive caregiver training program in the country.\r\n\r\n<img id="lmulogo" class="center-block" style="padding: 2em 1em 1em;" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/lm_university_logo.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/lm_university_logo.png\'" alt="" width="70%" height="auto" />\r\n\r\nOur Training Program offers an extensive array of courses that include:\r\n<table class="table table-striped">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="40%"><strong>Basic Training</strong></td>\r\n<td width="60%">Personal Care, Hygiene, Mobility and Transferring, Nutrition, and Home Management</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Health Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Comprehensive Competency Assessment by Staff RNs, Wound Care, Medication Assistance, CPR, UTI</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Disease Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Alzheimers, Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS), Parkinsons, Multiple Sclerosis, and Diabetes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Nutrition</strong></td>\r\n<td>Diabetic, Gluten Free, Low Sodium, Vegetarian, Kosher and Halal Diet Requirements</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Cultural Training </strong></td>\r\n<td>Communications and Interpersonal Training, Satisfaction, Hospitality</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>At-Risk Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Recognizing Depression</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Safety Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Oxygen Safety</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div  class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_09.jpg\');"></div>\r\n<div  class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="howwehire" class="anchor"></a>How We Hire</h1>\r\nYou can take comfort in knowing that all Lifematters employees have completed our rigorous hiring process that includes proprietary interviewing and testing protocols. 100% of Lifematters caregivers hold Certified Nursing Assistant Certificates or equivalent education and experience.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="col-xs-4" style="text-align: center;"><img class="img-circle gold_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/nursingassistantseal.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/nursingassistantseal.png\'" alt="" width="125" height="125" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-xs-4" style="text-align: center;"><img class="img-circle blue_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/registerednurseseal.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/registerednurseseal.png\'" alt="" width="125" height="125" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-xs-4" style="text-align: center;"><img class="img-circle teal_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/licensedpracticalnurse.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/licensedpracticalnurse.png\'" alt="" width="125" height="125" /></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEvery caregiver that works at Lifematters is an employee, not a sub-contractor. We vet our caregivers against multiple requirements before being hired.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Enhanced security background investigation</li>\r\n	<li>Criminal history search</li>\r\n	<li>Social Security Number trace</li>\r\n	<li>Motor vehicle report</li>\r\n	<li>Verification of CNA training and certification</li>\r\n	<li>Confirmation of U.S. employment eligibility</li>\r\n	<li>Personal and professional references</li>\r\n	<li>Multiple rounds of in-person panel interviews with HR, clinical, client services and corporate leadership team</li>\r\n	<li>Lifematters fees cover all employment wages and taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Lifematters employees have workers compensation and liability insurance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://lifematters.digitalhealthstrategies.com/joinourteam/"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn more about the Lifematters Team Culture and see a list of Open Positions <span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>', 'How We Work', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '101-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-15 11:37:21', '2014-09-15 11:37:21', '', 101, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/blog/101-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (470, 1, '2014-09-17 08:10:45', '2014-09-17 08:10:45', '<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_36.jpg\');"></div>\r\n<div class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue">Our Story</h1>\r\n<h2><a id="ourhistory" class="anchor"></a>Our History</h2>\r\nLifematters was founded with a single mission in mind – to dramatically improve the lives of clients by helping them manage their personal and health care needs in the comfort and privacy of their own homes.\r\n\r\nNow in its 10th year, Lifematters is the largest employer based home care company in the country with more than 4,000 satisfied clients. Our team consists of more than 1,200 active caregivers and a client service and corporate support staff of over 45 people.\r\n<div id="ourhistorytimeline" class="hidden-xs"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEstablished by CEO Scott Thompson in the autumn of 2004, Lifematters was the result of personal needs that Scott experienced when his family members required capable, compassionate, and skilled home care – and could not find it. Scott watched his aunt battle Alzheimer’s disease, and his father become deeply saddened when his mother (Scott’s grandmother) required nursing home care in a facility that did not offer a good quality of life. Scott saw a major need, and believed that the way to significantly improve home care was to change the way it was delivered. At the time that Lifematters was created, the vast majority of home care companies brought on independent contractors, rather than hire caregivers as actual employees. The founder and former CEO of a human resources and recruiting company, Scott knew that by hiring the right people and providing them with sound training and good benefits, he could ultimately provide better care for his and his employees’ families as well as for clients.\r\n\r\nAlways a firm believer that one can “do well by doing good”, Scott set out to build an organization that would create a win-win situation – for Lifematters’ clients, for clients’ families, and for Lifematters employees and the communities in which they serve. He knew what was required for this to happen – caregivers that were carefully chosen and then highly trained in basic as well as specialized areas; clients that would have the opportunity to be involved in decisions, including the level of care required as well as the selection of their caregiver(s); and a support system for both the clients and the caregivers that would ensure that the best possible care was consistently provided to keep people safe, comfortable, and cared for in their own homes.\r\n\r\nLifematters has successfully accomplished what Scott envisioned. Today, the company is the largest single-site, employer based, private duty home care company in the country, all in place for one reason only – to deliver un-compromised home care, provided by dedicated, skilled and highly trained caregivers that are backed by the full support of clinical, corporate and management teams, for professional, reliable and compassionate home care.\r\n\r\nAfter watching his mother suffer through the realities of nursing home living, Scott’s father asked for Scott’s promise to always ensure he would remain at home as he aged. Scott agreed -- he would never want to move his dad somewhere that would make him unhappy. And recently, Mr. Thompson had to undergo major, life-threatening surgery. Upon release from the hospital, he did in fact return to, and remain at, his home, with an occasional visit from a registered nurse, more frequent visits from licensed practical nurses, and the vast majority of time being cared for by CNAs that stayed by his side 24/7. He is now doing fine, and happy to still be residing, with his caregivers, in his own home.\r\n<h2>Our Mission, Vision and Values</h2>\r\n<h3><a id="ourmission" class="anchor"></a>Our Mission</h3>\r\n<h4>To dramatically improve the lives of our clients by helping them manage their personal and health care needs in the comfort and privacy of their homes.</h4>\r\n<h3>Our Vision</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To inspire our team to be the best they can be by creating an outstanding work environment.</li>\r\n	<li>To set the industry standard for world class service by anticipating and exceeding our clients’ desires and needs.</li>\r\n	<li>To create a culture that passionately meets the goals of our clients, community, associates and partners.</li>\r\n	<li>To be a highly effective team and fast moving entrepreneurial organization.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Our Values</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Growth and contribution</li>\r\n	<li>Service</li>\r\n	<li>Honesty</li>\r\n	<li>Innovation</li>\r\n	<li>Integrity</li>\r\n	<li>People</li>\r\n	<li>Excellence</li>\r\n	<li>Adaptability</li>\r\n	<li>Trust and respect</li>\r\n	<li>Personal accountability</li>\r\n	<li>Fun</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/affiliates.jpg\');"></div>\r\n<div class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="ourpartnersandaffiliates" class="anchor" title="Our Affiliates &amp; Partners"></a>Our Affiliates &amp; Partners</h1>\r\n<div class="row affiliations">\r\n<h3>AFFILIATIONS</h3>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/alzheimers_assoc.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nAlzheimer\'s Association\r\n<a href="http://alz.org" target="_blank"><h3>alz.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/apda.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nParkinson\'s Disease Association\r\n<a href="http://apdaparkinson.org" target="_blank"><h3>apdaparkinson.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/als_assoc.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nALS Association\r\n<a href="http://alsa.org" target="_blank"><h3>alsa.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/intl_pamds.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nThe Movement Disorders Society\r\n<a href="http://movementdisorders.org" target="_blank"><h3>movementdisorders.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/nmss.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nMultiple Sclerosis Society\r\n<a href="http://nationalmssociety.org" target="_blank"><h3>nationalmssociety.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/icava.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nInternational Council on Active Aging\r\n<a href="http://icaa.cc" target="_blank"><h3>icaa.cc</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row affiliations">\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/aarp.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nAmerican Association of Retired People\r\n<a href="http://aarp.org" target="_blank"><h3>aarp.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/nasmm.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nNational Association of Senior Move Managers\r\n<a href="http://nasmm.com" target="_blank"><h3>nasmm.com</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/napo.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nNational Association of Professional Organizers\r\n<a href="http://napo.net" target="_blank"><h3>napo.net</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/aagp.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nAmerican Association for Geriatric Psychiatry\r\n<a href="http://aagponline.org" target="_blank"><h3>aagponline.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row strategicpartners">\r\n<h3>STRATEGIC PARTNERS</h3>\r\nLifematters has strategic partnerships with several leading organizations in the home care and technology space.\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/cma_caremngt.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nCare Management Associates (CMA)\r\n<a href="http://cmacares.com" target="_blank"><h3>cmacares.com</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/trtmt_diaries.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nTreatment Diaries\r\n<a href="http://treatmentdiaries.com" target="_blank"><h3>treatmentdiaries.com</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/stratis.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nStratis Business Systems\r\n<a href="http://stratisinc.com" target="_blank"><h3>stratisinc.com</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/dhs.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nDigital Health Strategies\r\n<a href="http://digitalhealthstrategies.com" target="_blank"><h3>digitalhealthstrategies.com</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/homecareplus.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nHomecare Plus\r\n<a href="http://homecareplus.org" target="_blank"><h3>homecareplus.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class="row strategicpartners">\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/houseworks.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nHouse-Works\r\n<a href="http://house-works.com" target="_blank"><h3>house-works.com</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h3>Our Corporate Social Responsibility:</h3>\r\n<h4>We support a variety of non-profit organizations throughout the region and across the country.</h4>\r\n<ul class="section_end">\r\n	<li>ALS Association of DC/MD/VA – <a href="http://alsinfo.org" target="_blank">alsinfo.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Alzheimer’s Association – <a href="http://alz.org" target="_blank">alz.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Anti-Defamation League – <a href="http://adl.org" target="_blank">adl.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Kid Save International – <a href="http://kidsave.org" target="_blank">kidsave.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Holy Cross Hospital Foundation – <a href="http://holycrosshealth.org/foundation" target="_blank">holycrosshealth.org/foundation</a></li>\r\n	<li>Iona Senior Services of Washington – <a href="http://iona.org" target="_blank">iona.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Jesuit Community at Georgetown University – <a href="http://jesuits.georgetown.edu" target="_blank">jesuits.georgetown.edu</a></li>\r\n	<li>Leukemia &amp; Lymphoma Society – <a href="http://lls.org" target="_blank">lls.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Northwest Neighbors Village, Washington, DC – <a href="http://nwnv.org" target="_blank">nwnv.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Wounded Warriors Project – <a href="http://woundedwarriorproject.org" target="_blank">woundedwarriorproject.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Arlington Free Clinic – <a href="http://arlingtonfreeclinic.org" target="_blank">arlingtonfreeclinic.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Becky’s Fund – <a href="http://beckysfund.org" target="_blank">beckysfund.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Inova Health System Foundation – <a href="http://foundation.inova.org" target="_blank">foundation.inova.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Inova Loudoun Hospital - <a href="inova.org/patient-and-visitor-information/facilities/inova-loudoun-hospital">inova.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Arts for the Ages (to benefit the Alzheimer’s Association) - <a href="http://fineartamerica.com/events/art-for-the-ages.html">fineartamerica.com</a></li>\r\n	<li>Chevy Chase at Home – <a href="http://www.chevychaseathome.org">chevychaseathome.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>MedStar National Rehabilitation Hospital - <a href="https://www.medstarhealth.org/nrh/Pages/default.aspx">medstarhealth.org</a></li>\r\n	<li>Guide to Retirement Living - <a href="http://www.retirement-living.com/">retirement-living.com</a></li>\r\n	<li>Family Pass - <a href="http://familypassfairfax.org/" target="_blank">familypass.org</a></li>\r\n</ul>', 'Our Story', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '105-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-17 08:10:45', '2014-09-17 08:10:45', '', 105, 'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/blog/105-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (463, 1, '2014-09-17 07:50:36', '2014-09-17 07:50:36', '<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_36.jpg\'); background-position: center -85px;"></div>\r\n<div class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue">Our Story</h1>\r\n<h2><a id="ourhistory" class="anchor"></a>Our History</h2>\r\nLifematters was founded with a single mission in mind – to dramatically improve the lives of clients by helping them manage their personal and health care needs in the comfort and privacy of their own homes.\r\n\r\nNow in its 10th year, Lifematters is the largest employer based home care company in the country with more than 4,000 satisfied clients. Our team consists of more than 1,200 active caregivers and a client service and corporate support staff of over 45 people.\r\n<div id="ourhistorytimeline" class="hidden-xs"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEstablished by CEO Scott Thompson in the autumn of 2004, Lifematters was the result of personal needs that Scott experienced when his family members required capable, compassionate, and skilled home care – and could not find it. Scott watched his aunt battle Alzheimer’s disease, and his father become deeply saddened when his mother (Scott’s grandmother) required nursing home care in a facility that did not offer a good quality of life. Scott saw a major need, and believed that the way to significantly improve home care was to change the way it was delivered. At the time that Lifematters was created, the vast majority of home care companies brought on independent contractors, rather than hire caregivers as actual employees. The founder and former CEO of a human resources and recruiting company, Scott knew that by hiring the right people and providing them with sound training and good benefits, he could ultimately provide better care for his and his employees’ families as well as for