aregiver vetting process</td>\r\n<td>✓</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Customized matching</td>\r\n<td>✓</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>FlexCare presence</td>\r\n<td>✓</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Care / task tracking system</td>\r\n<td>Proprietary telephony system</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class="hidden-xs">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="50%">\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="qualityandexpertise" class="anchor" title="Quality and Expertise"></a>Quality and Expertise</h2>\r\nWe have the most highly qualified, experienced, and trained caregivers and care managers in the business. Our employees are thoroughly screened and meticulously selected to ensure they deliver on our industry-leading standards of quality and care. 100% of our caregivers hold Certified Nursing Assistant certificates or equivalent education and experience. And because we spend more time and energy on rigorous training for all of our CNAs, GNAs, and other staff, we’re able to hire and retain the best caregivers in the industry.</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="completecareservices" class="anchor" title="Complete Care Services"></a>Complete Care Services</h2>\r\nLifematters is one of a few home care companies that provides full-service capabilities in home care. From home care, to skilled nursing services, to highly-specialized care for chronic diseases such as dementia, Alzheimer’s, Diabetes, ALS, and Parkinson’s. Whatever your home care needs are, Lifematters can provide the solution.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 20px;"><a title="How We Work" href="http://lifematters.digitalhealthstrategies.com/howwework"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn more about Our Training Processes<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></td>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 20px;"><a title="How We Can Help" href="http://lifematters.digitalhealthstrategies.com/howwecanhelp/"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn More about How We Can Help<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="choice" class="anchor" title="Choice"></a>Choice</h2>\r\nNo one else gives you the ability to choose the exact caregiver you want from a group of the most qualified caregivers in the business, based on your unique care profile and requirements.</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="supportandreliability" class="anchor" title="24x7x365 Support and Reliability"></a>24x7x365 Support and Reliability</h2>\r\nWe know how essential good communication is to good care. Whether you have an emergency, need to schedule a caregiver immediately, change your existing schedule, or get answers to your questions, we are here 24x7, 365 days a year.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 20px;"><a title="How We Work" href="http://lifematters.digitalhealthstrategies.com/howwework"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn More about our Matching Process<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></td>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 20px;"><a title="Contact Us" href="http://lifematters.digitalhealthstrategies.com/contact-us/"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Contact Us Today<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="technologyandinnovation" class="anchor" title="Technology and Innovation"></a>Technology and Innovation</h2>\r\nWe use and provide the latest technologies to help guarantee our caregivers’ accountability. From ensuring on-time arrivals and end-of-shift departures through our automated telecom systems, to having the ability to provide you with state-of-the-art health and safety monitoring devices, Lifematters offers cutting edge technologies that ease and improve living.</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div class="visible-xs-block">\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="qualityandexpertise" class="anchor" title="Quality and Expertise"></a>Quality and Expertise</h2>\r\nWe have the most highly qualified, experienced, and trained caregivers and care managers in the business. Our employees are thoroughly screened and meticulously selected to ensure they deliver on our industry-leading standards of quality and care. 100% of our caregivers hold Certified Nursing Assistant certificates or equivalent education and experience. And because we spend more time and energy on rigorous training for all of our CNAs, GNAs, and other staff, we’re able to hire and retain the best caregivers in the industry.<a title="How We Work" href="http://lifematters.digitalhealthstrategies.com/howwework"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn more about Our Training Processes<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="completecareservices" class="anchor" title="Complete Care Services"></a>Complete Care Services</h2>\r\nLifematters is one of a few home care companies that provides full-service capabilities in home care. From home care, to skilled nursing services, to highly-specialized care for chronic diseases such as dementia, Alzheimer’s, Diabetes, ALS, and Parkinson’s. Whatever your home care needs are, Lifematters can provide the solution.<a title="How We Can Help" href="http://lifematters.digitalhealthstrategies.com/howwecanhelp/"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn More about How We Can Help<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="choice" class="anchor" title="Choice"></a>Choice</h2>\r\nNo one else gives you the ability to choose the exact caregiver you want from a group of the most qualified caregivers in the business, based on your unique care profile and requirements.<a title="How We Work" href="http://lifematters.digitalhealthstrategies.com/howwework"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn More about our Matching Process<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="supportandreliability" class="anchor" title="24x7x365 Support and Reliability"></a>24x7x365 Support and Reliability</h2>\r\nWe know how essential good communication is to good care. Whether you have an emergency, need to schedule a caregiver immediately, change your existing schedule, or get answers to your questions, we are here 24x7, 365 days a year.<a title="Contact Us" href="http://lifematters.digitalhealthstrategies.com/contact-us/"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Contact Us Today<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="technologyandinnovation" class="anchor" title="Technology and Innovation"></a>Technology and Innovation</h2>\r\nWe use and provide the latest technologies to help guarantee our caregivers’ accountability. From ensuring on-time arrivals and end-of-shift departures through our automated telecom systems, to having the ability to provide you with state-of-the-art health and safety monitoring devices, Lifematters offers cutting edge technologies that ease and improve living.</div>', 'The Lifematters Difference', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '109-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-15 13:47:34', '2014-09-15 13:47:34', '', 109, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/blog/109-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (343, 1, '2014-09-15 13:57:03', '2014-09-15 13:57:03', '<b>Job Summary:</b>\r\n\r\nWe are hiring RNs licensed in Washington, D.C., Maryland, and/or Virginia (we encourage certifications in all three locations) for office and/or case work. RNs provide direct client care services in the client’s home or the hospital by utilizing the nursing process and clinical knowledge to ensure high quality client care. This position is under the general supervision of the Director of Clinical Services and is responsible for one shift, eight hours/day and five days/week or as designated by the supervisor, or may be on an hourly basis. Nurses are subject to overtime, callback, and on-call as required and in conformance with wage and hour regulations. Lifematters’ RNs report to the Director of Clinical Services and/or a Nursing Supervisor.\r\n\r\n<strong>Responsibilities:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Assess the physical, psychosocial, spiritual, and environmental status of assigned clients in a systematic and continuous manner to provide required client services.</li>\r\n	<li>Consult with physicians, other staff, client/family, and other caregivers to formulate a plan of care and coordinate delivery of services to ensure high quality client care.</li>\r\n	<li>Provide home health/hospital nursing services in accordance with the plan of care and utilizing the nursing process.</li>\r\n	<li>Perform ongoing assessment of client’s status and response to services to evaluate the plan of care and modify as necessary.</li>\r\n	<li>Adhere to department and agency policies, procedures, and methods to increase the department’s contribution to the organization’s effectiveness.</li>\r\n	<li>Perform related accountabilities/responsibilities as required or directed.</li>\r\n	<li>Continuously evaluate the client’s status and work with client/caregiver in developing ways to meet their needs.</li>\r\n	<li>Coordinate and integrate services being provided to each client by all disciplines.</li>\r\n	<li>Initiate and revise client care plan for Nursing Assistants based on client’s needs and supervise the care provided by the Nursing Assistant as applicable.</li>\r\n	<li>Inform the physician and other healthcare team members of changes in the client’s conditions and needs.</li>\r\n	<li>Perform related accountabilities/responsibilities as required or directed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Qualifications:</b>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>One year (1) year experience as a professional nurse within the last three (3) years.</li>\r\n	<li>Completion of refresher course if applicant has not practiced in past five (5) years.</li>\r\n	<li>Current state licensure as a Registered Nurse.</li>\r\n	<li>Valid state driver’s license, current automobile insurance and reliable means of transportation.</li>\r\n	<li>Home care experience preferred. Ability to provide care in a variety of settings</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Registered Nurses (RNs)', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '250-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-09-15 13:57:03', '2014-09-15 13:57:03', '', 250, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/blog/250-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
