INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (406, 2, '2014-09-18 18:23:46', '2014-09-18 18:23:46', '<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/alternate_howwework.jpg\'); background-position: center -45px;"></div>\r\n<div class="container-sp-height  hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue">How We Work</h1>\r\nIn order to make your home care search and decision as simple and stress free as possible, we developed our unique Lifematters Care Plan Process. We help you identify the perfect caregiver for your family’s unique needs from our large pool of highly trained, licensed, and experienced candidates.\r\n\r\nFrom the minute you contact Lifematters, you are connected with a dedicated client services representative who will guide you every step of the way and ensure all of your questions and concerns are answered.\r\n\r\nOur staff takes a personal one-to-one approach with both clients and candidates, and we will work together to create a customized care plan that meets your requirements and delivers the care you need.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div  class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_14.jpg\'); background-position: center -150px;"></div>\r\n<div  class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="howwematch" class="anchor"></a>How We Match</h1>\r\nLifematters’ caregiver matching process combines information we learn from talking to you and your family with what we know from our decades of experience, resulting in the right plan and caregiver for you.\r\n\r\nUnique in our industry, Lifematters’ clients are directly involved in the selection of the caregiver. Beyond simply assigning an employee with the necessary skills, we invest as much time as necessary to match personalities and ensure that your caregiver is a perfect match.\r\n<div id="careplanprocess" class="container">\r\n<h2 class="orng" style="text-align: center;">THE LIFEMATTERS CARE PLAN PROCESS</h2>\r\n<p class="hidden-xs" style="text-align: center;"><em>Click the circles to learn about our process</em></p>\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div id="casestarts_circ" class="col-sm-3">\r\n<div class="img-circle">\r\n<h2>Case Starts</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="desc visible-xs-block">Call 1(800) 293-8973 or complete our online client registration; we will contact you within two hours and you will be connected with a dedicated Client Services Representative. We’ll discuss your situation and determine if you must act quickly. If your need is immediate, we can provide a temporary caregiver during the short time that Steps 2 and 3 are occurring.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="assesment_circ" class="col-sm-3">\r\n<div class="img-circle">\r\n<h2>Assessment</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="desc visible-xs-block">A Lifematters Client Service Representative interviews our potential client, family member or legal representative by telephone, e-mail or in person to get all the information necessary to complete a Lifematters Medical and Lifestyle Profile that will assist in selecting the right caregiver.<br>Interview categories include:<ul><li>Name and address</li><li>Nicknames and how you would like to be addressed</li><li>Age</li><li>Present living arrangements</li><li>Name of friends and relatives</li><li>Family involvement in current lifestyle</li><li>Former or present occupation</li><li>Daily routine</li><li>Lifetime accomplishments</li><li>Social activities</li><li>Leisure activities</li><li>Review of medical history</li><li>Current level of physical mobility</li><li>Type of assistance needed</li><li>Any use of medical equipment</li><li>Mental status</li><li>Any outside support services currently being used</li><li>Scope of services required by Lifematters</li><li>Type and qualifications of personnel</li><li>Potential schedule</li><li>Start of service date</li></ul></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="matching_circ" class="col-sm-3">\r\n<div class="img-circle">\r\n<h2>Matching</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="desc visible-xs-block">After we discuss and assess your needs, we will create a list of experienced caregivers whose skillsets and demeanor best match your needs based on:<ul><li>License, scope of practice</li><li>Experience, skills assessment scores</li><li>Transportation availability</li><li>Location</li><li>Hours available based on client’s requirements</li><li>Personality</li></ul>After reviewing the list, Lifematters Client Services and Clinical teams work together to select and assign the most appropriate caregiver. If requested, clients can then schedule in-person interviews in order to assure a perfect match.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="carebegins_circ" class="col-sm-3">\r\n<div class="img-circle">\r\n<h2>Care Begins</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="desc visible-xs-block">We will send you a complete welcome kit containing all of the information you need, and together we will confirm a start-of-care date. A Lifematters Registered Nurse will schedule and also complete a detailed assessment and caregiving plan. Once your caregiver has begun working with your family, you will receive a follow-up assessment by a Lifematters Registered Nurse on a regularly scheduled and periodic, ongoing basis to monitor progress and make adjustments as necessary. To ensure that our caregivers continue to provide our standard exemplary level of care, ongoing check-ins by our home care quality and relationship experts will take place for the length of our engagement.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="hwwddes"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div  class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_16.jpg\'); background-position: center -110px;"></div>\r\n<div  class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="howwetrain" class="anchor"></a>How We Train</h1>\r\nOur product is our people, so our team is our most important asset. Each of our caregivers undergoes hours of training developed by Lifematters University – the most comprehensive caregiver training program in the country.\r\n\r\n<img id="lmulogo" class="center-block" style="padding: 2em 1em 1em;" src="http://www.lifemattersusa.com/img/lm_university_logo.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/img/lm_university_logo.png\'" alt="" width="70%" height="auto" />\r\n\r\nOur Training Program offers an extensive array of courses that include:\r\n<table class="table table-striped">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="40%"><strong>Basic Training</strong></td>\r\n<td width="60%">Personal Care, Hygiene, Mobility and Transferring, Nutrition, and Home Management</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Health Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Comprehensive Competency Assessment by Staff RNs, Wound Care, Medication Assistance, CPR, UTI</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Disease Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Alzheimers, Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS), Parkinsons, Multiple Sclerosis, and Diabetes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Nutrition</strong></td>\r\n<td>Diabetic, Gluten Free, Low Sodium, Vegetarian, Kosher and Halal Diet Requirements</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Cultural Training </strong></td>\r\n<td>Communications and Interpersonal Training, Satisfaction, Hospitality</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>At-Risk Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Recognizing Depression</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Safety Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Oxygen Safety</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div  class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_09.jpg\'); background-position: center -110px;"></div>\r\n<div  class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="howwehire" class="anchor"></a>How We Hire</h1>\r\nYou can take comfort in knowing that all Lifematters employees have completed our rigorous hiring process that includes proprietary interviewing and testing protocols. 100% of Lifematters caregivers hold Certified Nursing Assistant Certificates or equivalent education and experience.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="col-xs-4" style="text-align: center;"><img class="img-circle gold_bg" src="http://www.lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/nursingassistantseal.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/nursingassistantseal.png\'" alt="" width="125" height="125" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-xs-4" style="text-align: center;"><img class="img-circle blue_bg" src="http://www.lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/registerednurseseal.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/registerednurseseal.png\'" alt="" width="125" height="125" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-xs-4" style="text-align: center;"><img class="img-circle teal_bg" src="http://www.lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/licensedpracticalnurse.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/licensedpracticalnurse.png\'" alt="" width="125" height="125" /></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEvery caregiver that works at Lifematters is an employee, not a sub-contractor. We vet our caregivers against multiple requirements before being hired.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Enhanced security background investigation</li>\r\n	<li>Criminal history search</li>\r\n	<li>Social Security Number trace</li>\r\n	<li>Motor vehicle report</li>\r\n	<li>Verification of CNA training and certification</li>\r\n	<li>Confirmation of U.S. employment eligibility</li>\r\n	<li>Personal and professional references</li>\r\n	<li>Multiple rounds of in-person panel interviews with HR, clinical, client services and corporate leadership team</li>\r\n	<li>Lifematters fees cover all employment wages and taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Lifematters employees have workers compensation and liability insurance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://www.lifemattersusa.com/joinourteam/"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn more about the Lifematters Team Culture and see a list of Open Positions <span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>', 'How We Work', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '101-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-09-18 18:23:46', '2014-09-18 18:23:46', '', 101, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/blog/101-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (407, 1, '2014-09-15 17:40:01', '2014-09-15 17:40:01', '<div class="container">\r\n<div class="row home_vid">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12 bdy">\r\n<h3 class="hdr blue"><span class="orng">LifeMatters:</span> Delivering Peace of Mind</h3>\r\nOver the past decade, Lifematters has become the first choice for home care in Maryland, Washington, D.C. and Northern Virginia. We work with our clients to create fully customized care plans staffed by our team of highly trained and skilled caregivers that deliver on a full range of in-home services.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">\r\n<div id="vidthumb" class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9"><img class="img-responsive aligncenter" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lifematters_video_titlecard.jpg" alt="" width="661" height="371" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container-fluid quote green_bg green_tx">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">We provide consistent, top quality service for both customers and employees through a unique combination of compassionate care, reliability and professionalism. That\'s the Lifematters Difference.\r\n<a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/thelifemattersdifference"><button class="hrz_btnB wht_bg">Learn More About What Sets Us Apart<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></div></blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container site-content">\r\n<div class="row home_sp howwecanhelp">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12 hdr">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle blue_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/hands.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/hands.png\'" alt="Icon" width="100" height="100" />\r\n<h1 class="blue">How We Can Help</h1>\r\n\r\n<hr class="blue_bg" />\r\n\r\nIt’s not just about being at home. It\'s about living as well as possible at home. Lifematters offers a full range of in-home services ranging from personal companionship to medical care, including general home management, nutrition and meals, mobility activities, and skilled nursing care. Whatever your needs, Lifematters will work with you to create and deliver on the right care plan. You will be supported by a full care team consisting of your caregiver and dedicated team members from client services, clinical care and corporate leadership. <a class="readmore" title="How We Can Help" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwecanhelp/">Read more</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl" style="margin-left: 11%;">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle green_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/homecare.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/homecare.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>Home Care</h3>\r\nStay safe, well and happy in the comfort of your home with the support of our certified caregivers.     <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwecanhelp#homecare"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle red_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/skillednursing.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/skillednursing.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>Skilled Nursing</h3>\r\nGet the clinical care you require from our team of RNs and LPNs. <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwecanhelp#skillednursing"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle orng_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/diseasespecialties.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/diseasespecialties.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>Disease Specialties</h3>\r\nReceive highly trained and specialized care for your disease or chronic condition.   <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwecanhelp#diseasespecialties"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle gold_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/flexcare.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/flexcare.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>Flexcare</h3>\r\nMaintain an independent lifestyle at your continuing care residential community with our on-site services. <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwecanhelp#flexcare"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container-fluid quote gold_bg gold_tx">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">"I knew the decision I was about to make for my family was huge, and you made it easy. I want to commend Lifematters and the staff you have hired and trained for making our experience a smooth one." - Julie <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/testimonials"><button class="hrz_btnB wht_bg">Read Our Testimonials<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></div></blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container site-content">\r\n<div class="row home_sp">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12 hdr">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle blue_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/gears.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/gears.png\'" alt="Icon" width="100" height="100" />\r\n<h1 class="blue">How We Work</h1>\r\n\r\n<hr class="blue_bg" />\r\n\r\nFinding the right care for you or a loved one can be overwhelming. But we are here to help you navigate this difficult process every step of the way. Our care management experts and client services team have spent decades working with families in need of home care. With the <em>Lifematters Care Plan Process</em>, you will get the necessary answers and solutions, whether you simply want guidance through the home care maze or urgently need a caregiver at your home today. <a class="readmore" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwework">Read more</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl" style="margin-left: 21%;">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle gold_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/howwematch.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/howwematch.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>How We Match</h3>\r\nWith our proprietary matching process, you receive a customized care plan and caregiver based on your specific needs, requests and situation. <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwework#howwematch"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle red_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/howwetrain.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/howwetrain.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>How We Train</h3>\r\nOur employees must complete our extensive Lifematters University training curriculum that sets the standard for the industry. <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwework#howwetrain"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle orng_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/howwehire.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/howwehire.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>How We Hire</h3>\r\nWe hire only the top 20% of applicants who pass our rigorous vetting, interviewing and testing qualifications. <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwework#howwehire"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container-fluid quote teal_bg teal_tx">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">“Carl was not just Dad\'s caregiver. He was his friend. He gently pushed him to do more than he thought he could do. Carl is our angel.” - Mrs. D <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/testimonials"><button class="hrz_btnB wht_bg">Read Our Testimonials<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></div></blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container site-content">\r\n<div class="row home_sp" style="padding-bottom: 10px;">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12 hdr">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle blue_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/whoweare.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/whoweare.png\'" alt="Icon" width="100" height="100" />\r\n<h1 class="blue">Who We Are</h1>\r\n\r\n<hr class="blue_bg" />\r\n\r\nOur people are our most valuable asset. The Lifematters team, all of whom live in the Washington DC metropolitan area, bring decades of proven experience in home care. We have more than 1,000 employees, but maintain a close-knit and familial environment. Each Lifematters employee has a unique background and skill set that adds value to our collective whole.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style="margin-bottom: 30px;"><a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/whoweare"><button class="hrz_btnA green_bg wht" style="padding-left: 4em; padding-right: 4em;">Meet Our Team</button></a></div>\r\n<div id="caregiverspotlight" class="container-fluid">\r\n<div class="container">\r\n<h1 class="hdr">Caregiver Spotlight</h1>\r\n<p class="body">We are pleased and proud to introduce you to a few of our caregivers who have been identified by their supervisors, clients, and clients’ family members as consistently providing exemplary service and showing strong dedication. Always reliable, professional and compassionate, they are wonderful examples of the Lifematters Difference. Be sure to visit this site again soon to meet more of our caregivers.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-4 col-md-3">\r\n<div class="staff_thumbnail">\r\n\r\n<img class="img-rounded img-responsive" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/briana_watford_donohoe.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n<h3 class="name">Briana Watford-Donohoe, LPN</h3>\r\n<button class="hrz_btnA orng_bg">Read More</button>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n\r\nBriana Watford-Donohoe, LPN, joined Lifematters as the Nurse/Manager of our Wellness Office at a Lifematters Flexcare facility in Washington, D.C. Prior to Lifematters, she gained extensive experience working at a nursing home in New York. Briana is a superb nurse with outstanding clinical skills and keen insights into the physical, medical and emotional challenges her clients face. She has forged highly positive relationships with the staff of the residences, the many physicians that call on the facility, and the Lifematters employees that she supervises, all of which makes for a great team of support to the residents in the building. Briana is a strong advocate for her clients, and is always there with a smiling face when they need a friend. Lifematters is proud to have Briana as our representative in the building.\r\n\r\n<strong>A word from Briana:</strong> “It’s just my nature to want to take care of people. When I’m not working, I’m caring for my young son. I never want to see anyone in pain, or hurt, or sad. So I love being able to prevent that, and to make sure our residents are comfortable, safe, and happy. I am so happy working with Lifematters! If I ever am experiencing an issue or have a question, there is always someone to back me up, support me, and help me figure it out. I’m never alone or on my own. The fact is, Lifematters is like a big family; everyone ends up knowing each other and helping each other out. It’s really terrific.”\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-4 col-md-3">\r\n<div class="staff_thumbnail">\r\n\r\n<img class="img-rounded img-responsive" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/constance_kwaah.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n<h3 class="name">Constance Kwaah, CNA, GNA</h3>\r\n<button class="hrz_btnA orng_bg">Read More</button>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n\r\nConstance Kwaah was hired by HouseWorks in 2009 and came to Lifematters when it acquired HouseWorks’ Maryland Office in December 2012. She has been a licensed Certified Nursing Aide (CNA) and Geriatric Nursing Assistant (GNA) since 2005, and has completed more than 3,000 hours, working with 10 clients, since joining Lifematters in 2012. Currently, Constance has three different clients for whom she works every day, every week. The clients and their families love her, and say she goes above and beyond at all times. We receive regular accolades about Constance -- in addition to being on time, compliant with policies, reporting issues and concerns, she is always helpful, caring, reliable and consistent.\r\n\r\n<strong>A word from Constance:</strong> “I genuinely want to help people – it’s what I do; it’s what Lifematters does. I love doing it. I have three children who I also love very much. And working for Lifematters is wonderful! The client services directors and coordinators are terrific – they are always there for me, willing to talk and listen and help as much as they can whenever I need something. It makes my job so very pleasant, and makes some of the tougher things we all have to deal with on occasion so much easier to handle.”\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-4 col-md-3">\r\n<div class="staff_thumbnail">\r\n\r\n<img class="img-rounded img-responsive" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/akberet_yohannas.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n<h3 class="name">Akberet Yohannas, HHA</h3>\r\n<button class="hrz_btnA orng_bg">Read More</button>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n\r\nAkberet Yohannas (“Yohannas”), according to her supervisor, always gives 110%; she fully dedicates herself to her position, and there is nothing she won’t do to make sure that the residents are well cared for. Exceptionally helpful, Yohannas is the type of person anyone would enjoy working with. A Lifematters employee since 2011, she has garnered affection and respect from her clients, their families, and her colleagues. Says her supervisor, “I just love working with her!”\r\n\r\n<strong>A Word from Yohannas:</strong> “I really enjoy my job. I love my clients – they are so very nice, and I have learned so much from them. And so, I do my very best for them – whatever I do for my clients, I strive to do it perfectly, always! And I love Lifematters – it’s a great company to work for! I’m a very blessed person, with a wonderful job and a wonderful family – I have four children and five grandchildren! I’m very lucky indeed.”\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-xs-6 col-sm-4 col-md-3">\r\n<div class="staff_thumbnail">\r\n\r\n<img class="img-rounded img-responsive" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/abdulai_dukaray.jpg" alt="" />\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n<h3 class="name">Abdulai Dukaray, CNA</h3>\r\n<button class="hrz_btnA orng_bg">Read More</button>\r\n<div class="bio">\r\n\r\nAbdulai is consistently praised by all of his clients for his professional attitude, cool and calm demeanor, and the exemplary care he provides. Rich Willis, a Lifematters’ Client Services Director in our Virginia office, has not heard one complaint about Abdulai during his time as an employee of Lifematters. He says that Abdulai consistently goes above and beyond to make sure the client and the client’s family are pleased with the service Lifematters is providing.\r\n\r\n<strong>A word from Abdulai:</strong>“Being a CNA requires great compassion – if you don’t feel love for what you are doing, you can’t do it well. If you are a caregiver only to earn an income, it won’t work – it is not about the money, it’s about the compassion. I’m an emotional guy, and it gives me great pleasure to help ensure my clients are happy and comfortable. And Lifematters is a great place to work. The staff is kind and helpful in assigning work to me and giving me important information about each client before I start the job so I can be the best I can be for that client. Because of all of the wonderful experience I am gaining from working for Lifematters, I feel I have a great future; I attended medical school in Sierra Leone (my home), and hope to become a doctor in the U.S. some day. I’m a pretty determined person and know that if I persevere, it will happen.”\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container-fluid quote red_bg red_tx">\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<div class="col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1 col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">“Your CNAs and LPNs were a very caring and professional team, assisting our family under crisis conditions with vigilance.” - Betty <a class="readmore" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/testimonials"><button class="hrz_btnB wht_bg">Read Our Testimonials <span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></div></blockquote>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container site-content">\r\n<div class="row home_sp our_story">\r\n<div class="col-lg-12 hdr">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle blue_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/ourstory.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/ourstory.png\'" alt="Icon" width="100" height="100" />\r\n<h1 class="blue">Our Story</h1>\r\n\r\n<hr class="blue_bg" />\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle green_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/ourhistory.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/ourhistory.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>Our History</h3>\r\nRead about our local origins and how we\'ve grown to become the largest employer based home care company in the DC region.     <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/ourstory#ourhistory"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle red_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/affiliations.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/affiliations.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>Affiliations</h3>\r\nLearn about our network of non-profit alliances and how they add to the Lifematters Difference.     <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/ourstory#ourpartnersandaffiliates"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle gold_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/locations.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/locations.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>Locations</h3>\r\nGet in touch and find our corporate locations across DC, Maryland and Virginia.<a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/contactus#officelocations"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle teal_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/jobs.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/jobs.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>Join Our Team</h3>\r\nLearn about why Lifematters is a great place to work and search available positions.       <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/joinourteam"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="vrtpnl">\r\n\r\n<img class="hdricon img-circle orng_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/blog.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/blog.png\'" alt="Icon" width="86" height="86" />\r\n<h3>Blog</h3>\r\nKeep up with the latest news, information and resources from the world of home care.       <a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/blog"><button class="hrz_btnA blue_bg">Read More</button></a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="container awards">\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<h3>Awards</h3>\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img style="max-width: 65%;" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/awards_inc500.jpg" alt="" width="100%" height="auto" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img style="max-width: 55%;" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/awards_bethesda.jpg" alt="" width="100%" height="auto" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img style="max-width: 90%; margin-top: 2em;" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/awards_future50.jpg" alt="" width="100%" height="auto" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-3"><img style="max-width: 55%;" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/awards_gazette.jpg" alt="" width="100%" height="auto" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', 'Home', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '88-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-15 17:40:01', '2014-09-15 17:40:01', '', 88, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/blog/88-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (409, 1, '2014-09-15 19:20:16', '2014-09-15 19:20:16', '<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_23.jpg\'); background-position-y: -120px;"></div>\r\n<div class="container-sp-height  hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue">How We Work</h1>\r\nIn order to make your home care search and decision as simple and stress free as possible, we developed our unique Lifematters Care Plan Process. We help you identify the perfect caregiver for your family’s unique needs from our large pool of highly trained, licensed, and experienced candidates.\r\n\r\nFrom the minute you contact Lifematters, you are connected with a dedicated client services representative who will guide you every step of the way and ensure all of your questions and concerns are answered.\r\n\r\nOur staff takes a personal one-to-one approach with both clients and candidates, and we will work together to create a customized care plan that meets your requirements and delivers the care you need.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div  class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_14.jpg\'); background-position-y: -160px; "></div>\r\n<div  class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="howwematch" class="anchor"></a>How We Match</h1>\r\nLifematters’ caregiver matching process combines information we learn from talking to you and your family with what we know from our decades of experience, resulting in the right plan and caregiver for you.\r\n\r\nUnique in our industry, Lifematters’ clients are directly involved in the selection of the caregiver. Beyond simply assigning an employee with the necessary skills, we invest as much time as necessary to match personalities and ensure that your caregiver is a perfect match.\r\n<div id="careplanprocess" class="container">\r\n<h2 class="orng" style="text-align: center;">THE LIFEMATTERS CARE PLAN PROCESS</h2>\r\n<p class="hidden-xs" style="text-align: center;"><em>Click the circles to learn about our process</em></p>\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div id="casestarts_circ" class="col-sm-3">\r\n<div class="img-circle">\r\n<h2>Case Starts</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="desc visible-xs-block">Call 1(800) 293-8973 or complete our online client registration; we will contact you within two hours and you will be connected with a dedicated Client Services Representative. We’ll discuss your situation and determine if you must act quickly. If your need is immediate, we can provide a temporary caregiver during the short time that Steps 2 and 3 are occurring.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="assesment_circ" class="col-sm-3">\r\n<div class="img-circle">\r\n<h2>Assessment</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="desc visible-xs-block">A Lifematters Client Service Representative interviews our potential client, family member or legal representative by telephone, e-mail or in person to get all the information necessary to complete a Lifematters Medical and Lifestyle Profile that will assist in selecting the right caregiver.<br>Interview categories include:<ul><li>Name and address</li><li>Nicknames and how you would like to be addressed</li><li>Age</li><li>Present living arrangements</li><li>Name of friends and relatives</li><li>Family involvement in current lifestyle</li><li>Former or present occupation</li><li>Daily routine</li><li>Lifetime accomplishments</li><li>Social activities</li><li>Leisure activities</li><li>Review of medical history</li><li>Current level of physical mobility</li><li>Type of assistance needed</li><li>Any use of medical equipment</li><li>Mental status</li><li>Any outside support services currently being used</li><li>Scope of services required by Lifematters</li><li>Type and qualifications of personnel</li><li>Potential schedule</li><li>Start of service date</li></ul></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="matching_circ" class="col-sm-3">\r\n<div class="img-circle">\r\n<h2>Matching</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="desc visible-xs-block">After we discuss and assess your needs, we will create a list of experienced caregivers whose skillsets and demeanor best match your needs based on:<ul><li>License, scope of practice</li><li>Experience, skills assessment scores</li><li>Transportation availability</li><li>Location</li><li>Hours available based on client’s requirements</li><li>Personality</li></ul>After reviewing the list, Lifematters Client Services and Clinical teams work together to select and assign the most appropriate caregiver. If requested, clients can then schedule in-person interviews in order to assure a perfect match.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="carebegins_circ" class="col-sm-3">\r\n<div class="img-circle">\r\n<h2>Care Begins</h2>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="desc visible-xs-block">We will send you a complete welcome kit containing all of the information you need, and together we will confirm a start-of-care date. A Lifematters Registered Nurse will schedule and also complete a detailed assessment and caregiving plan. Once your caregiver has begun working with your family, you will receive a follow-up assessment by a Lifematters Registered Nurse on a regularly scheduled and periodic, ongoing basis to monitor progress and make adjustments as necessary. To ensure that our caregivers continue to provide our standard exemplary level of care, ongoing check-ins by our home care quality and relationship experts will take place for the length of our engagement.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id="hwwddes"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div  class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_16.jpg\'); background-position-y: -100px;"></div>\r\n<div  class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="howwetrain" class="anchor"></a>How We Train</h1>\r\nOur product is our people, so our team is our most important asset. Each of our caregivers undergoes hours of training developed by Lifematters University – the most comprehensive caregiver training program in the country.\r\n\r\n<img id="lmulogo" class="center-block" style="padding: 2em 1em 1em;" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/lm_university_logo.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/lm_university_logo.png\'" alt="" width="70%" height="auto" />\r\n\r\nOur Training Program offers an extensive array of courses that include:\r\n<table class="table table-striped">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="40%"><strong>Basic Training</strong></td>\r\n<td width="60%">Personal Care, Hygiene, Mobility and Transferring, Nutrition, and Home Management</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Health Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Comprehensive Competency Assessment by Staff RNs, Wound Care, Medication Assistance, CPR, UTI</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Disease Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Alzheimers, Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS), Parkinsons, Multiple Sclerosis, and Diabetes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Nutrition</strong></td>\r\n<td>Diabetic, Gluten Free, Low Sodium, Vegetarian, Kosher and Halal Diet Requirements</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Cultural Training </strong></td>\r\n<td>Communications and Interpersonal Training, Satisfaction, Hospitality</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>At-Risk Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Recognizing Depression</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Safety Training</strong></td>\r\n<td>Oxygen Safety</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div  class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_09.jpg\'); background-position-y: -140px;"></div>\r\n<div  class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="howwehire" class="anchor"></a>How We Hire</h1>\r\nYou can take comfort in knowing that all Lifematters employees have completed our rigorous hiring process that includes proprietary interviewing and testing protocols. 100% of Lifematters caregivers hold Certified Nursing Assistant Certificates or equivalent education and experience.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="col-xs-4" style="text-align: center;"><img class="img-circle gold_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/nursingassistantseal.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/nursingassistantseal.png\'" alt="" width="125" height="125" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-xs-4" style="text-align: center;"><img class="img-circle blue_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/registerednurseseal.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/registerednurseseal.png\'" alt="" width="125" height="125" /></div>\r\n<div class="col-xs-4" style="text-align: center;"><img class="img-circle teal_bg" src="http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/licensedpracticalnurse.svg" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src=\'http://lifemattersusa.com/img/icons/licensedpracticalnurse.png\'" alt="" width="125" height="125" /></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEvery caregiver that works at Lifematters is an employee, not a sub-contractor. We vet our caregivers against multiple requirements before being hired.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Enhanced security background investigation</li>\r\n	<li>Criminal history search</li>\r\n	<li>Social Security Number trace</li>\r\n	<li>Motor vehicle report</li>\r\n	<li>Verification of CNA training and certification</li>\r\n	<li>Confirmation of U.S. employment eligibility</li>\r\n	<li>Personal and professional references</li>\r\n	<li>Multiple rounds of in-person panel interviews with HR, clinical, client services and corporate leadership team</li>\r\n	<li>Lifematters fees cover all employment wages and taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Lifematters employees have workers compensation and liability insurance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://lifemattersusa.com/joinourteam/"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn more about the Lifematters Team Culture and see a list of Open Positions <span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>', 'How We Work', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '101-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-15 19:20:16', '2014-09-15 19:20:16', '', 101, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/blog/101-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (410, 1, '2014-09-15 19:25:40', '2014-09-15 19:25:40', '<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_36.jpg\'); background-position-y:-85px;"></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue">Our Story</h1>\r\n<h2><a id="ourhistory" class="anchor"></a>Our History</h2>\r\nLifematters was founded with a single mission in mind – to dramatically improve the lives of clients by helping them manage their personal and health care needs in the comfort and privacy of their own homes.\r\n\r\nNow in its 10th year, Lifematters is the largest employer based home care company in the country with more than 4,000 satisfied clients. Our team consists of more than 1,200 active caregivers and a client service and corporate support staff of over 45 people.\r\n\r\n<div id="ourhistorytimeline" class="hidden-xs"></div>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEstablished by CEO Scott Thompson in the autumn of 2004, Lifematters was the result of personal needs that Scott experienced when his family members required capable, compassionate, and skilled home care – and could not find it. Scott watched his aunt battle Alzheimer’s disease, and his father become deeply saddened when his mother (Scott’s grandmother) required nursing home care in a facility that did not offer a good quality of life. Scott saw a major need, and believed that the way to significantly improve home care was to change the way it was delivered. At the time that Lifematters was created, the vast majority of home care companies brought on independent contractors, rather than hire caregivers as actual employees. The founder and former CEO of a human resources and recruiting company, Scott knew that by hiring the right people and providing them with sound training and good benefits, he could ultimately provide better care for his and his employees’ families as well as for clients.\r\n\r\nAlways a firm believer that one can “do well by doing good”, Scott set out to build an organization that would create a win-win situation – for Lifematters’ clients, for clients’ families, and for Lifematters employees and the communities in which they serve. He knew what was required for this to happen – caregivers that were carefully chosen and then highly trained in basic as well as specialized areas; clients that would have the opportunity to be involved in decisions, including the level of care required as well as the selection of their caregiver(s); and a support system for both the clients and the caregivers that would ensure that the best possible care was consistently provided to keep people safe, comfortable, and cared for in their own homes.\r\n\r\nLifematters has successfully accomplished what Scott envisioned. Today, the company is the largest single-site, employer based, private duty home care company in the country, all in place for one reason only – to deliver un-compromised home care, provided by dedicated, skilled and highly trained caregivers that are backed by the full support of clinical, corporate and management teams, for professional, reliable and compassionate home care.\r\n\r\nAfter watching his mother suffer through the realities of nursing home living, Scott’s father asked for Scott’s promise to always ensure he would remain at home as he aged.  Scott agreed -- he would never want to move his dad somewhere that would make him unhappy.  And recently, Mr. Thompson had to undergo major, life-threatening surgery. Upon release from the hospital, he did in fact return to, and remain at, his home, with an occasional visit from a registered nurse, more frequent visits from licensed practical nurses, and the vast majority of time being cared for by CNAs that stayed by his side 24/7.  He is now doing fine, and happy to still be residing, with his caregivers, in his own home.\r\n<h2>Our Mission, Vision and Values</h2>\r\n<h3><a id="ourmission" class="anchor"></a>Our Mission</h3>\r\n<h4>To dramatically improve the lives of our clients by helping them manage their personal and health care needs in the comfort and privacy of their homes.</h4>\r\n<h3>Our Vision</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To inspire our team to be the best they can be by creating an outstanding work environment.</li>\r\n	<li>To set the industry standard for world class service by anticipating and exceeding our clients’ desires and needs.</li>\r\n	<li>To create a culture that passionately meets the goals of our clients, community, associates and partners.</li>\r\n	<li>To be a highly effective team and fast moving entrepreneurial organization.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Our Values</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Growth and contribution</li>\r\n	<li>Service</li>\r\n	<li>Honesty</li>\r\n	<li>Innovation</li>\r\n	<li>Integrity</li>\r\n	<li>People</li>\r\n	<li>Excellence</li>\r\n	<li>Adaptability</li>\r\n	<li>Trust and respect</li>\r\n	<li>Personal accountability</li>\r\n	<li>Fun</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/affiliates.jpg\'); background-position-y: -150px;"></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="ourpartnersandaffiliates" class="anchor" title="Our Affiliates &amp; Partners"></a>Our Affiliates &amp; Partners</h1>\r\n<div class="row affiliations">\r\n<h3>AFFILIATIONS</h3>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/alzheimers_assoc.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nAlzheimer\'s Association\r\n<a href="http://alz.org" target="_blank"><h3>alz.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/apda.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nParkinson\'s Disea