ting your PDF once you\'ve filled it out completely, save the document to your computer, then open it in Adobe Reader (PDF Software).</span> <strong><a title="Download Adobe Reader FREE" href="http://get.adobe.com/reader" target="_blank">Download it here</a></strong> for free if needed.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Using your printer</strong>, print out the document, and fill out by hand with a dark inked pen.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li>Submit your application by either:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Clicking the "Submit" or "Submit form" buttons</strong> within the PDF (Must use Adobe Reader for buttons to function)</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Emailing your completed application</strong> as an attachment to <a href="mailto:apply@lifemattersusa.com" target="_blank">apply@lifemattersusa.com</a></li>\r\n	<li><strong>Faxing your application</strong> to (301) 652-7215</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n	<li> Your application will be then reviewed by our Human Resources team, and we will contact you if a match that complements your skills, experiences, and indicated availability is found amongst our current hiring needs.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="panel panel-default">\r\n<div class="panel-body"><button class="btn btn-link reqs important" type="button" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#joinModal"><img class="pull-left" src="http://lifematters.digitalhealthstrategies.com/wp-content/themes/LifeMattersUSA.com/img/icons/important_blk.svg" alt="" width="30px" height="auto" />Important: CNA, GNA, LPN and RN applicants click here to read important application requirements.</button></div>\r\n</div>', 'Join Our Team', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '103-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-15 20:20:49', '2014-09-15 20:20:49', '', 103, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/blog/103-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (423, 1, '2014-09-15 20:22:08', '2014-09-15 20:22:08', '<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/IMG_0319.jpg\'); background-position: center -110px;"></div>\r\n<div class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue">The Lifematters Difference</h1>\r\nWe understand how vital your family and loved ones are to you. After all, each of us is a son or daughter, spouse, parent, sister, brother or friend.\r\n\r\nWe are here because we have a passionate commitment to deliver the quality of care that we would expect and require for our own family and loved ones.\r\n\r\nLifematters’ mission is to dramatically improve the lives of our clients by helping them manage their personal and health care needs in the comfort and privacy of their own homes.\r\n\r\nScroll down to learn about our differentiators and what makes us the best choice for your home care needs.\r\n<table id="lmd" class="table table-striped" style="min-height: 352px;">\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th width="50%">Credential</th>\r\n<th width="50%">Lifematters</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="50%">Employed Caregivers with insurance, workers’ compensation</td>\r\n<td width="50%">✓</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Dedicated Client Service, Clinical Team, Management &amp; Support</td>\r\n<td>✓</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Local Presence &amp; Independently Owned</td>\r\n<td>✓</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Awards</td>\r\n<td>Inc 500, Gazette, Bethesda Magazine, SmartCEO</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Training</td>\r\n<td>Lifematters University</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Type of care</td>\r\n<td>Home Care, Skilled Nursing, FlexCare</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Specialization of care</td>\r\n<td>Alzheimer’s, ALS, Dementia, Diabetes and more</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td># of caregivers</td>\r\n<td>1,000+</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>RN assessment</td>\r\n<td>✓</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Caregiver vetting process</td>\r\n<td>✓</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Customized matching</td>\r\n<td>✓</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>FlexCare presence</td>\r\n<td>✓</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Care / task tracking system</td>\r\n<td>Proprietary telephony system</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table class="hidden-xs">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width="50%">\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="qualityandexpertise" class="anchor" title="Quality and Expertise"></a>Quality and Expertise</h2>\r\nWe have the most highly qualified, experienced, and trained caregivers and care managers in the business. Our employees are thoroughly screened and meticulously selected to ensure they deliver on our industry-leading standards of quality and care. 100% of our caregivers hold Certified Nursing Assistant certificates or equivalent education and experience. And because we spend more time and energy on rigorous training for all of our CNAs, GNAs, and other staff, we’re able to hire and retain the best caregivers in the industry.</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="completecareservices" class="anchor" title="Complete Care Services"></a>Complete Care Services</h2>\r\nLifematters is one of a few home care companies that provides full-service capabilities in home care. From home care, to skilled nursing services, to highly-specialized care for chronic diseases such as dementia, Alzheimer’s, Diabetes, ALS, and Parkinson’s. Whatever your home care needs are, Lifematters can provide the solution.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 20px;"><a title="How We Work" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwework"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn more about Our Training Processes<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></td>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 20px;"><a title="How We Can Help" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwecanhelp/"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn More about How We Can Help<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="choice" class="anchor" title="Choice"></a>Choice</h2>\r\nNo one else gives you the ability to choose the exact caregiver you want from a group of the most qualified caregivers in the business, based on your unique care profile and requirements.</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="supportandreliability" class="anchor" title="24x7x365 Support and Reliability"></a>24x7x365 Support and Reliability</h2>\r\nWe know how essential good communication is to good care. Whether you have an emergency, need to schedule a caregiver immediately, change your existing schedule, or get answers to your questions, we are here 24x7, 365 days a year.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 20px;"><a title="How We Work" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwework"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn More about our Matching Process<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></td>\r\n<td style="padding-top: 20px;"><a title="Contact Us" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/contactus/"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Contact Us Today<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="technologyandinnovation" class="anchor" title="Technology and Innovation"></a>Technology and Innovation</h2>\r\nWe use and provide the latest technologies to help guarantee our caregivers’ accountability. From ensuring on-time arrivals and end-of-shift departures through our automated telecom systems, to having the ability to provide you with state-of-the-art health and safety monitoring devices, Lifematters offers cutting edge technologies that ease and improve living.</td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<div class="visible-xs-block">\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="qualityandexpertise" class="anchor" title="Quality and Expertise"></a>Quality and Expertise</h2>\r\nWe have the most highly qualified, experienced, and trained caregivers and care managers in the business. Our employees are thoroughly screened and meticulously selected to ensure they deliver on our industry-leading standards of quality and care. 100% of our caregivers hold Certified Nursing Assistant certificates or equivalent education and experience. And because we spend more time and energy on rigorous training for all of our CNAs, GNAs, and other staff, we’re able to hire and retain the best caregivers in the industry.<a title="How We Work" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwework"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn more about Our Training Processes<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="completecareservices" class="anchor" title="Complete Care Services"></a>Complete Care Services</h2>\r\nLifematters is one of a few home care companies that provides full-service capabilities in home care. From home care, to skilled nursing services, to highly-specialized care for chronic diseases such as dementia, Alzheimer’s, Diabetes, ALS, and Parkinson’s. Whatever your home care needs are, Lifematters can provide the solution.<a title="How We Can Help" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwecanhelp/"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn More about How We Can Help<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="choice" class="anchor" title="Choice"></a>Choice</h2>\r\nNo one else gives you the ability to choose the exact caregiver you want from a group of the most qualified caregivers in the business, based on your unique care profile and requirements.<a title="How We Work" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/howwework"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Learn More about our Matching Process<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="supportandreliability" class="anchor" title="24x7x365 Support and Reliability"></a>24x7x365 Support and Reliability</h2>\r\nWe know how essential good communication is to good care. Whether you have an emergency, need to schedule a caregiver immediately, change your existing schedule, or get answers to your questions, we are here 24x7, 365 days a year.<a title="Contact Us" href="http://lifemattersusa.com/contactus"><button class="hrz_btnB ltgrey_bg">Contact Us Today<span class="arw_sym">▶</span></button></a>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="blue"><a id="technologyandinnovation" class="anchor" title="Technology and Innovation"></a>Technology and Innovation</h2>\r\nWe use and provide the latest technologies to help guarantee our caregivers’ accountability. From ensuring on-time arrivals and end-of-shift departures through our automated telecom systems, to having the ability to provide you with state-of-the-art health and safety monitoring devices, Lifematters offers cutting edge technologies that ease and improve living.</div>', 'The Lifematters Difference', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '109-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-15 20:22:08', '2014-09-15 20:22:08', '', 109, 'http://lifemattersusa.com/blog/109-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (424, 1, '2014-09-15 20:22:41', '2014-09-15 20:22:41', '<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_36.jpg\'); background-position: center -85px;"></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue">Our Story</h1>\r\n<h2><a id="ourhistory" class="anchor"></a>Our History</h2>\r\nLifematters was founded with a single mission in mind – to dramatically improve the lives of clients by helping them manage their personal and health care needs in the comfort and privacy of their own homes.\r\n\r\nNow in its 10th year, Lifematters is the largest employer based home care company in the country with more than 4,000 satisfied clients. Our team consists of more than 1,200 active caregivers and a client service and corporate support staff of over 45 people.\r\n\r\n<div id="ourhistorytimeline" class="hidden-xs"></div>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEstablished by CEO Scott Thompson in the autumn of 2004, Lifematters was the result of personal needs that Scott experienced when his family members required capable, compassionate, and skilled home care – and could not find it. Scott watched his aunt battle Alzheimer’s disease, and his father become deeply saddened when his mother (Scott’s grandmother) required nursing home care in a facility that did not offer a good quality of life. Scott saw a major need, and believed that the way to significantly improve home care was to change the way it was delivered. At the time that Lifematters was created, the vast majority of home care companies brought on independent contractors, rather than hire caregivers as actual employees. The founder and former CEO of a human resources and recruiting company, Scott knew that by hiring the right people and providing them with sound training and good benefits, he could ultimately provide better care for his and his employees’ families as well as for clients.\r\n\r\nAlways a firm believer that one can “do well by doing good”, Scott set out to build an organization that would create a win-win situation – for Lifematters’ clients, for clients’ families, and for Lifematters employees and the communities in which they serve. He knew what was required for this to happen – caregivers that were carefully chosen and then highly trained in basic as well as specialized areas; clients that would have the opportunity to be involved in decisions, including the level of care required as well as the selection of their caregiver(s); and a support system for both the clients and the caregivers that would ensure that the best possible care was consistently provided to keep people safe, comfortable, and cared for in their own homes.\r\n\r\nLifematters has successfully accomplished what Scott envisioned. Today, the company is the largest single-site, employer based, private duty home care company in the country, all in place for one reason only – to deliver un-compromised home care, provided by dedicated, skilled and highly trained caregivers that are backed by the full support of clinical, corporate and management teams, for professional, reliable and compassionate home care.\r\n\r\nAfter watching his mother suffer through the realities of nursing home living, Scott’s father asked for Scott’s promise to always ensure he would remain at home as he aged.  Scott agreed -- he would never want to move his dad somewhere that would make him unhappy.  And recently, Mr. Thompson had to undergo major, life-threatening surgery. Upon release from the hospital, he did in fact return to, and remain at, his home, with an occasional visit from a registered nurse, more frequent visits from licensed practical nurses, and the vast majority of time being cared for by CNAs that stayed by his side 24/7.  He is now doing fine, and happy to still be residing, with his caregivers, in his own home.\r\n<h2>Our Mission, Vision and Values</h2>\r\n<h3><a id="ourmission" class="anchor"></a>Our Mission</h3>\r\n<h4>To dramatically improve the lives of our clients by helping them manage their personal and health care needs in the comfort and privacy of their homes.</h4>\r\n<h3>Our Vision</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To inspire our team to be the best they can be by creating an outstanding work environment.</li>\r\n	<li>To set the industry standard for world class service by anticipating and exceeding our clients’ desires and needs.</li>\r\n	<li>To create a culture that passionately meets the goals of our clients, community, associates and partners.</li>\r\n	<li>To be a highly effective team and fast moving entrepreneurial organization.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Our Values</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Growth and contribution</li>\r\n	<li>Service</li>\r\n	<li>Honesty</li>\r\n	<li>Innovation</li>\r\n	<li>Integrity</li>\r\n	<li>People</li>\r\n	<li>Excellence</li>\r\n	<li>Adaptability</li>\r\n	<li>Trust and respect</li>\r\n	<li>Personal accountability</li>\r\n	<li>Fun</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/affiliates.jpg\'); background-position: center  -150px;"></div>\r\n\r\n<div class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="ourpartnersandaffiliates" class="anchor" title="Our Affiliates &amp; Partners"></a>Our Affiliates &amp; Partners</h1>\r\n<div class="row affiliations">\r\n<h3>AFFILIATIONS</h3>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/alzheimers_assoc.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nAlzheimer\'s Association\r\n<a href="http://alz.org" target="_blank"><h3>alz.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/apda.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nParkinson\'s Disease Association\r\n<a href="http://apdaparkinson.org" target="_blank"><h3>apdaparkinson.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/als_assoc.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nALS Association\r\n<a href="http://alsa.org" target="_blank"><h3>alsa.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/intl_pamds.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nThe Movement Disorders Society\r\n<a href="http://movementdisorders.org" target="_blank"><h3>movementdisorders.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/nmss.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nMultiple Sclerosis Society\r\n<a href="http://nationalmssociety.org" target="_blank"><h3>nationalmssociety.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/icava.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nInternational Council on Active Aging\r\n<a href="http://icaa.cc" target="_blank"><h3>icaa.cc</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row affiliations">\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/aarp.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nAmerican Association of Retired People\r\n<a href="http://aarp.org" target="_blank"><h3>aarp.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/nasmm.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nNational Association of Senior Move Managers\r\n<a href="http://nasmm.com" target="_blank"><h3>nasmm.com</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/napo.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nNational Association of Professional Organizers\r\n<a href="http://napo.net" target="_blank"><h3>napo.net</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/aagp.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nAmerican Association for Geriatric Psychiatry\r\n<a href="http://aagponline.org" target="_blank"><h3>aagponline.org</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/leadingage.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nLeading Age\r\n<a href="http://leadingage.com" target="_blank"><h3>leadingage.com</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="row strategicpartners">\r\n<a href="http://" target="_blank"><h3>STRATEGIC PARTNERS</h3></a>\r\nLifematters has strategic partnerships with several leading organizations in the home care and technology space.\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/cma_caremngt.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nCare Management Associates (CMA)\r\n<a href="http://cmacares.com" target="_blank"><h3>cmacares.com</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-md-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/trtmt_diaries.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nTreatment Diaries\r\n<a href="http://treatmentdiaries.com" target="_blank"><h3>treatmentdiaries.com</h3></a>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\