INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (455, 1, '2014-09-17 06:57:39', '2014-09-17 06:57:39', '<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/lm_offices_july2014_36.jpg\'); background-position: center -85px;"></div>\r\n<div class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue">Our Story</h1>\r\n<h2><a id="ourhistory" class="anchor"></a>Our History</h2>\r\nLifematters was founded with a single mission in mind – to dramatically improve the lives of clients by helping them manage their personal and health care needs in the comfort and privacy of their own homes.\r\n\r\nNow in its 10th year, Lifematters is the largest employer based home care company in the country with more than 4,000 satisfied clients. Our team consists of more than 1,200 active caregivers and a client service and corporate support staff of over 45 people.\r\n<div id="ourhistorytimeline" class="hidden-xs"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEstablished by CEO Scott Thompson in the autumn of 2004, Lifematters was the result of personal needs that Scott experienced when his family members required capable, compassionate, and skilled home care – and could not find it. Scott watched his aunt battle Alzheimer’s disease, and his father become deeply saddened when his mother (Scott’s grandmother) required nursing home care in a facility that did not offer a good quality of life. Scott saw a major need, and believed that the way to significantly improve home care was to change the way it was delivered. At the time that Lifematters was created, the vast majority of home care companies brought on independent contractors, rather than hire caregivers as actual employees. The founder and former CEO of a human resources and recruiting company, Scott knew that by hiring the right people and providing them with sound training and good benefits, he could ultimately provide better care for his and his employees’ families as well as for clients.\r\n\r\nAlways a firm believer that one can “do well by doing good”, Scott set out to build an organization that would create a win-win situation – for Lifematters’ clients, for clients’ families, and for Lifematters employees and the communities in which they serve. He knew what was required for this to happen – caregivers that were carefully chosen and then highly trained in basic as well as specialized areas; clients that would have the opportunity to be involved in decisions, including the level of care required as well as the selection of their caregiver(s); and a support system for both the clients and the caregivers that would ensure that the best possible care was consistently provided to keep people safe, comfortable, and cared for in their own homes.\r\n\r\nLifematters has successfully accomplished what Scott envisioned. Today, the company is the largest single-site, employer based, private duty home care company in the country, all in place for one reason only – to deliver un-compromised home care, provided by dedicated, skilled and highly trained caregivers that are backed by the full support of clinical, corporate and management teams, for professional, reliable and compassionate home care.\r\n\r\nAfter watching his mother suffer through the realities of nursing home living, Scott’s father asked for Scott’s promise to always ensure he would remain at home as he aged. Scott agreed -- he would never want to move his dad somewhere that would make him unhappy. And recently, Mr. Thompson had to undergo major, life-threatening surgery. Upon release from the hospital, he did in fact return to, and remain at, his home, with an occasional visit from a registered nurse, more frequent visits from licensed practical nurses, and the vast majority of time being cared for by CNAs that stayed by his side 24/7. He is now doing fine, and happy to still be residing, with his caregivers, in his own home.\r\n<h2>Our Mission, Vision and Values</h2>\r\n<h3><a id="ourmission" class="anchor"></a>Our Mission</h3>\r\n<h4>To dramatically improve the lives of our clients by helping them manage their personal and health care needs in the comfort and privacy of their homes.</h4>\r\n<h3>Our Vision</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To inspire our team to be the best they can be by creating an outstanding work environment.</li>\r\n	<li>To set the industry standard for world class service by anticipating and exceeding our clients’ desires and needs.</li>\r\n	<li>To create a culture that passionately meets the goals of our clients, community, associates and partners.</li>\r\n	<li>To be a highly effective team and fast moving entrepreneurial organization.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Our Values</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Growth and contribution</li>\r\n	<li>Service</li>\r\n	<li>Honesty</li>\r\n	<li>Innovation</li>\r\n	<li>Integrity</li>\r\n	<li>People</li>\r\n	<li>Excellence</li>\r\n	<li>Adaptability</li>\r\n	<li>Trust and respect</li>\r\n	<li>Personal accountability</li>\r\n	<li>Fun</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div class="container-sp hidden-xs" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/affiliates.jpg\'); background-position: center  -150px;"></div>\r\n<div class="container-sp-height hidden-xs"></div>\r\n<h1 class="blue"><a id="ourpartnersandaffiliates" class="anchor" title="Our Affiliates &amp; Partners"></a>Our Affiliates &amp; Partners</h1>\r\n<div class="row affiliations">\r\n<h3>AFFILIATIONS</h3>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/alzheimers_assoc.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nAlzheimer\'s Association\r\n<a href="http://alz.org" target="_blank">\r\n</a>\r\n<h3>alz.org</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class="col-sm-2 affllogo">\r\n<div class="thumb" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/apda.png\');"></div>\r\n<div class="caption">\r\n\r\nParki