Assessment and monitoring</li>\r\n	<li>Education and advocacy</li>\r\n	<li>Family caregiver coaching</li>\r\n	<li>Planning and problem solving</li>\r\n	<li>Caregiving services</li>\r\n	<li>Lifematters can be an employees’ “one stop solution” to help with their caregiving needs. Employers can offer Lifematters services to their employees, knowing they are providing a unique and valuable benefit.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a title="Contact Us" href="http://www.lifemattersusa.com/contactus/">Contact Us</a> if you are interested in learning more about this program.', 'How We Can Help', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '99-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-09-18 06:33:15', '2014-09-18 06:33:15', '', 99, 'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/blog/99-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
INSERT IGNORE INTO `wp_0r3t7cj3av_posts` VALUES (533, 2, '2014-09-18 16:02:05', '2014-09-18 16:02:05', 'Abdulai is consistently praised by all of his clients for his professional attitude, cool and calm demeanor, and the exemplary care he provides. Rich Willis, a Lifematters’ Client Services Director in our Virginia office, has not heard one complaint about Abdulai during his time as an employee of Lifematters. He says that Abdulai consistently goes above and beyond to make sure the client and the client’s family are pleased with the service Lifematters is providing.\r\n\r\n<strong>A word from Abdulai:</strong> Being a CNA requires great compassion – if you don’t feel love for what you are doing, you can’t do it well. If you are a caregiver only to earn an income, it won’t work – it is not about the money, it’s about the compassion. I’m an emotional guy, and it gives me great pleasure to help ensure my clients are happy and comfortable. And Lifematters is a great place to work. The staff is kind and helpful in assigning work to me and giving me important information about each client before I start the job so I can be the best I can be for that client. Because of all of the wonderful experience I am gaining from working for Lifematters, I feel I have a great future; I attended medical school in Sierra Leone (my home), and hope to become a doctor in the U.S. some day. I’m a pretty determined person and know that if I persevere, it will happen.”', 'Abdulai Dukaray, CNA', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '166-autosave-v1', '', '', '2014-09-18 16:02:05', '2014-09-18 16:02:05', '', 166, 'http://www.lifemattersusa.com/blog/166-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0); 
